# Component Patterns

## Islands architecture

React components run as Astro islands. They must be hydrated with a `client:*` directive in `.astro` files:

```astro
<Navigation client:load />        <!-- Needs immediate interactivity (nav, mobile menu) -->
<PageModules client:load />        <!-- Module renderer needs React state -->
<SomeWidget client:visible />      <!-- Below fold — hydrate when scrolled into view -->
```

Never import React components directly without a `client:` directive in Astro — they won't hydrate.

## Module component pattern

Every page module follows this structure:

```tsx
"use client";

export interface <Name>Props {
  theme?: string;
  // ... fields matching the Sanity schema
}

export function <Name>({ theme = "cream", ...props }: <Name>Props) {
  return (
    <section data-theme={theme} style={{ background: "var(--section-bg)" }}>
      <div className="pp-container pp-section">
        {/* content */}
      </div>
    </section>
  );
}
```

Key rules:
- `"use client"` directive at top of file
- `data-theme` on the outermost `<section>` — drives CSS variables
- `pp-container` for max-width centering
- `pp-section` for vertical padding
- Props interface mirrors the Sanity module schema fields
- Provide sensible defaults for all props (content editors may leave fields empty)

## ModuleRenderer

`ModuleRenderer.tsx` maps `_type` to components via a switch. When adding a new module:

1. Import the component
2. Add a `case "<type>":` returning the component with spread props

## Layout components

- `Navigation`: fixed top, transparent -> solid on scroll, mobile Sheet at `lg:` breakpoint
- `Footer`: multi-column layout from siteSettings

Both accept props shaped to match `SITE_SETTINGS_QUERY_RESULT`.

## Styling conventions

- Use Tailwind utility classes as the primary styling method
- Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` for conditional class merging
- Use design system CSS classes (`.eyebrow`, `.section-title`, `.btn-primary`) for brand consistency
- Avoid inline `style` except for `background: var(--section-bg)` on themed sections
- Icons: use `lucide-react` — already installed

## Type safety

- Component props should align with Sanity types from `sanity.types.ts`
- Handle `null | undefined` from Sanity — use `??` defaults and optional chaining
- Filter arrays with null items before rendering (see `filterLinks()` in Navigation)
